description: D.N. ½ inch white plumbers Teflon tape or thread seal tape is a simple but highly versatile thread sealant, used primarily in ductwork and piping applications. PTFE stands for polytetrafluoroethylene. It is essentially a long strip of synthetic polymer film sold on a spool. One key material characteristic of this Sealant Tape is the fact that it is water-repellant. This makes thread Tape incredibly useful for a wide range of plumbing and pipework jobs - which is why you will find a thread seal tape of some kind in almost every well-stocked pipework or plumbing too. Thread Tape plumbing stop leaks, water Sealant Tape is Perfect for showerheads, Pipe Sealing, and Pipe Threads. Robust pressure resistance makes this product suitable for use in high-bar applications like fuel injection systems. Non-stick backing makes it easy to reapply later or remove, without having to clean messy adhesive from the inside surfaces of duct joints and pipe threads. This white Teflon tape (PTFE) thread seal tape is compatible with metal or plastic piping (up to 1-1/2” diameter) for water, most chemicals, hydraulic line, air, sewage, and sprinkler piping.
